By Ngozi Njoku Lagos – The police on Tuesday arraigned a  21-year-man, Seunfunmi Oluwabiyi, in an Ogudu Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for allegedly defaming the General Overseer of World Bible Church, Ajelogo, Mr Juluis  Kumoluyi . Oluwabiyi, whose address, was not provided, is charged with breach of peace, to which he pleaded not guilty. The prosecutor, Insp Lucky Ihiehie told the court that the dedendant
committed the offence in January at  the World Bible Church, Ajelogo,
Mile 12, Lagos. Ihiehie alleged that the defendant, went about telling people in the
church that the Kumoluyi was sleeping with a female member of the
church. He said the defendant conducted himself in a manner that was likely to breach the peace. Ihiehie said the offence contravened the provisions of Section 168 (d) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mrs Bukola Mogaji, admitted the accused to bail in the sum of N20, 000  with one surety in like sum. Mogaji adjourned the case untill May 5.